m><SubItem><Name>DiscreteMotion</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>512</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>ContinuousMotion</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>520</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>SynchronizedMotion</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>528</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Homing</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>536</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>ConstantVelocity</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ additional status - (PLCopen definition)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>544</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Accelerating</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>552</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Decelerating</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>560</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Operational</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Axis.NcToPlc.StateDWord ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>568</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>ControlLoopClosed</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ operational and position control active ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>576</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>HasJob</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>584</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>HasBeenStopped</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>592</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>NewTargetPosition</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ new target position commanded during move ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>600</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>InPositionArea</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>608</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>InTargetPosition</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>616</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Homed</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>624</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>HomingBusy</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>632</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>MotionCommandsLocked</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ stop 'n hold ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>640</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>SoftLimitMinExceeded</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ reverse soft travel limit exceeded ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>648</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>SoftLimitMaxExceeded</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ forward soft travel limit exceeded ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>656</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Moving</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>664</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>PositiveDirection</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>672</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>NegativeDirection</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>680</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>NotMoving</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>688</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Compensating</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ superposition - overlayed motion ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>696</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>ExtSetPointGenEnabled</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>704</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>ExternalLatchValid</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>712</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>CamDataQueued</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>720</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>CamTableQueued</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>728</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>CamScalingPending</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>736</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>CmdBuffered</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>744</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>PTPmode</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>752</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>DriveDeviceError</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>760</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>IoDataInvalid</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>768</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Coupled</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Axis.NcToPlc.CoupleState ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>776</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>OpMode</Name><Type Namespace="TcoDrivesBeckhoff">TcoAxisOpModes</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ axis operation mode feedback from NcToPlc ]]></Comment><BitSize>96</BitSize><BitOffs>784</BitOffs></SubItem></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoDrivesBeckhoff">eHomingMode</Name><BitSize>16</BitSize><BaseType>INT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text>MC_DefaultHoming</Text><Enum>0</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>MC_Direct</Text><Enum>4</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>MC_ForceCalibration</Text><Enum>7</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>MC_ResetCalibration</Text><Enum>8</Enum></EnumInfo></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoDrivesBeckhoff">eEncoderReferenceMode</Name><BitSize>32</BitSize><BaseType>UDINT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text>ENCODERREFERENCEMODE_DEFAULT</Text><Enum>0</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>ENCODERREFERENCEMODE_PLCCAM</Text><Enum>1</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>ENCODERREFERENCEMODE_HARDWARESYNC</Text><Enum>2</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>ENCODERREFERENCEMODE_HARDWARELATCHPOS</Text><Enum>3</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>ENCODERREFERENCEMODE_HARDWARELATCHNEG</Text><Enum>4</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>ENCODERREFERENCEMODE_SOFTWARESYNC</Text><Enum>5</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>ENCODERREFERENCEMODE_SOFTDRIVELATCHPOS</Text><Enum>6</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>ENCODERREFERENCEMODE_SOFTDRIVELATCHNEG</Text><Enum>7</Enum></EnumInfo></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoObjectRestorer</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType GUID="{18071995-0000-0000-0000-000000000018}">PVOID</ExtendsType><Method><Name>RestoreObject</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Ensures calling the <c>Restore()</c> method on the object entered.	
			<para>
				<example>
				<note type="Example">
				<para>
					Possibility to use the fluent syntax.
				</para>
					<code>ChangeState(newState).RestoreObject(myFirstChildObject).RestoreObject(mySecondChildObject);</code>
				 </note>
				</example>
			</para>		
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoObjectRestorer</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>Obj</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoRestorable</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoState</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoObject</ExtendsType><Method><Name>__getIsAutoRestoreEnabled</Name><ReturnType>BOOL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>8</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__getLastStateChangeCycle</Name><ReturnType>ULINT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__getState</Name><ReturnType>INT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>16</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>RestoreObject</Name><ReturnType Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoObjectRestorer</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>Obj</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoRestorable</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceId</Name><Value>1098</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoCore">TcoStateBase</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Provides basic state controller. It could be implemented using <c>IF</c>, <c>IF</c> <c>ELSIF</c> or <c>CASE</c> statement. The transition to the different state needs to be perfromed by calling 
			<see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoStateBase.ChangeState(Object)"/> method. This method ensures also calling the <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoStateBase.OnStateChange(Object,Object)"/> every time that state is changed. The 
		  	<c>OnStateChange()</c>could be overloaded and some custom code that needs to be executed on each change of the state could be placed here. The TcoState could be used like this:
			<para>
				<example>
				<note type="Example 1">
				<para>
					<c>_myTask()</c> is not a member of this <c>TcoState()</c>, it is restored manually to be able to trigger it in the next state.
				</para>
					<code>
						IF State = 10 THEN
							Main._myTask.Invoke();
							Main._myTask.Execute();
							IF Main._myTask.Done THEN
								ChangeState(State + 10);
								Main._myTask.Restore();
							END_IF
						END_IF
						IF State = 20 THEN
							Main._myTask.Invoke();
							Main._myTask.Execute();
							IF Main._myTask.Done THEN
								ChangeState(State + 10);
								Main._myTask.Restore();
							END_IF
						END_IF
					</code>
				 </note>
				</example>
			</para>		
			<para>
				<example>
				<note type="Example 2">
				<para>
					<c>_myTask()</c> is a member of this <c>TcoState()</c>, it is restored manually using the fluent syntax to be able to trigger it in the next state.
				</para>
					<code>
						CASE State OF
							10:	
							_myTask.Invoke();
							_myTask.Execute();
							IF _myTask.Done THEN
								ChangeState(State + 10).RestoreObject(_myTask);
							END_IF
							20:
							_myTask.Invoke();
							_myTask.Execute();
							IF _myTask.Done THEN
								ChangeState(State + 10).RestoreObject(_myTask);
							END_IF	
						END_CASE
					</code>
				 </note>
				</example>
				<para>
					See <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoState.RestoreObject(Object)"/> for more details.
				</para>
			</para>			
		</summary>		
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><BitSize>7232</BitSize><ExtendsType Namespace="TcoCore">TcoObject</ExtendsType><Implements Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoState</Implements><Implements Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoObjectRestorer</Implements><SubItem><Name>_State</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>6912</BitOffs></SubItem><Method><Name>__getState</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Return actual state of this instance. Needs to be asked for cyclically in case of this instance is auto restorable.
			<para>
				See also <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoStateBase.AutoRestorable()"/>
			</para>
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType>INT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>16</ReturnBitSize><Local><Name>State</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Local><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>OnStateChange</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			This method is called on each change of the <c>State</c>. This method could be overloaded and custom code should be placed here.	
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>PreviousState</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>NewState</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>__getAutoRestorable</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Returns if this instance is auto restorable. This is 'dependency property'. Value of this property is given by the parent of this object. 
			This value is assigned after download by calling the implicit method <c>FB_init()</c> of the parent object and cannot be changed during runtime.
			The <c>AutoRestorable</c> property of this objects is retrieved from the <c>EnableAutoRestore</c> property of the parent object.
			This is done by calling the <c>CheckIfAutoRestoreEnabledByParent()</c> method inside the implicit method <c>FB_init()</c> after download.
			If this instance is the auto restorable it will call the <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoState.Restore()"/> method if:
			<para>
				1.) This instance has not been called for one or more cycles and starts to be called again. (By calling the instance means asking for its property <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoState.State()"/> property).
			</para>
			<para>
				2.)	Parent object of this instance changes its state.
			</para>
			<para>
				See also <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoState.EnableAutoRestore()"/>
			</para>
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType>BOOL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>8</ReturnBitSize><Local><Name>AutoRestorable</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Local><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>ChangeStateProtected</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Use to change the State property of this instance to the new value. This method is final, so it cannot be overloaded. However there is a <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoState.OnStateChange(Object,Object)"/> 
			method that is called on each change of the <c>State</c> and could be overloaded.
			<para>
				<example>
				<note type="Example">
				<para>
					Possibility to use the fluent syntax.
				</para>
					<code>ChangeState(newState).RestoreObject(myChildObject);</code>
				 </note>
				</example>
			</para>		
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoState</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>NewState</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Local><Name>PreviousState</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Local></Method><Method><Name>__getContext</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Returns the context of the parent object, that this object is assigned to.
			This context is given by declaration, its value is assigned after download by calling the implicit method <c>FB_init()</c> and cannot be changed during runtime.
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoContext</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Local><Name>Context</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoContext</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>AutoRestore</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Private method called each time that State property is asked for. If this instance is auto restorable, this method ensures calling the <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoState.Restore()"/> method if:
			<para>
				1.)	Parent object of this instance changes its state in this Plc cycle.
			</para>
			<para>
				2.)	Parent object of this instance changes its state no mather when and this instance has not yet process this change.
			</para>
			<para>
				3.) This instance has not been called for one or more cycles and starts to be called again. (By calling the instance means asking for its property <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoState.State()"/> property).
			</para>
			<para>
				See also <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoState.AutoRestorable()"/>
			</para>
			<para>
				See also <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoState.EnableAutoRestore()"/>
			</para>
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><Local><Name>_MyParent_TcoState</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoState</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>_MyParent_ChangeStateCycle</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>_MyParent_LastChangeState</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Local></Method><Method><Name>__getLastStateChangeCycle</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Returns number of the Plc cycle during which this instance changes its <c>State</c> last time.
			The child objects ask for this value to ensure auto restore mechanism working.  	
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType>ULINT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Local><Name>LastStateChangeCycle</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>Restore</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Restores this instance to the state -1.
			<para>
				<example>
					<note type="Example">
						<para>
							Possibility to use the fluent syntax.
						</para>
						<code>
							Restore().RestoreObject(myFirstChildObject).RestoreObject(mySecondChildObject);
						</code>
					 </note>
				</example>
			</para>				
			<para>
				See also <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoState.AutoRestorable()"/>
			</para>
			<para>
				See also <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoState.EnableAutoRestore()"/>
			</para>
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoRestorable</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize></Method><Method><Name>__getIsAutoRestoreEnabled</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Returns if the auto restore mechanism is enabled for this instance. This property does not affect this instance, but it affects all members of this instance.
			If the auto restore is enabled, the child member call its <c>Restore()</c> method if:
			<para>
			1.) Its instance has not been called for one or more cycles.
			</para>
			<para>
			2.)	Its parent object (THIS^ instance) has changed its state.
			</para>
			This value is assigned after download by calling the implicit method <c>FB_init()</c> and cannot be changed during runtime.
			<para>
				See also <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoStateBase.AutoRestorable()"/>
			</para>
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType>BOOL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>8</ReturnBitSize><Local><Name>IsAutoRestoreEnabled</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Local><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>RestoreObject</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Ensures the call of the <c>Restore()</c> method in fluent-like fashion.	
			<para>
				<example>
				<note type="Example">
				<para>
					Possibility to use the fluent syntax.
				</para>
					<code>ChangeState(newState).RestoreObject(myFirstChildObject).RestoreObject(mySecondChildObject);</code>
				 </note>
				</example>
			</para>		
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoObjectRestorer</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>Obj</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoRestorable</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>CheckIfCalledCyclically</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Private method called each time that the <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoStateBase.State()"/> property is asked for. 
			If this instance is auto restorable, this method ensures calling the <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoStateBase.Restore()"/> method if
			this instance has not been called for one or more cycles and starts to be called again. (By calling the instance means asking for its property State).
			<para>
				See also <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoStateBase.AutoRestorable"/>
			</para>
			<para>
				See also <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoStateBase.EnableAutoRestore"/>
			</para>
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><Local><Name>_MyContextStartCycleCount</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local></Method><Method><Name>CheckIfAutoRestoreEnabledByParent</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
