e><BitOffs>3006016</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_jerk</Name><Type>LREAL</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><BitOffs>3006080</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_inString</Name><Type>STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>648</BitSize><BitOffs>3006144</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_done</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>3006792</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_arranged</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>3006800</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_axis1Disabled</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>3006808</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_axis2Disabled</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>3006816</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_axis3Disabled</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>3006824</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_axis4Disabled</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>3006832</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_axisReferenceType</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>3006848</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_positions</Name><Type>SomeTestMultiPositions</Type><BitSize>9280</BitSize><BitOffs>3006912</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_moveParam</Name><Type Namespace="TcoDrivesBeckhoff">TcoMultiAxisMoveParam</Type><BitSize>1280</BitSize><BitOffs>3016192</BitOffs></SubItem><Method><Name>Main</Name></Method><Properties><Property><Name>PouType</Name><Value>FunctionBlock</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoCore">TcoStateExtendible</Name><BitSize>7232</BitSize><ExtendsType Namespace="TcoCore">TcoStateBase</ExtendsType><Method><Name>OnStateChange</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			This method is called on each change of the <c>State</c>. This method could be overloaded and custom code should be placed here.	
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>PreviousState</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>NewState</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>ChangeState</Name><ReturnType Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoState</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>NewState</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>PouType</Name><Value>FunctionBlock</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoCore">eStepStatus</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Describes the step status inside the sequencer.
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><BitSize>16</BitSize><BaseType>INT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text>None</Text><Enum>0</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			No status defined.
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>Disabled</Text><Enum>10</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Step is disabled and won't be executed.
			Next enabled step in the sequence will be executed, when the sequencer reaches that step.
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>ReadyToRun</Text><Enum>20</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Step is ready to run. This case occurs when sequence is in step mode, step is in order of the execution and step is enabled.
			The body statements of the current step's are not executing. After calling StepIn method, step starts running the statements.
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>Running</Text><Enum>30</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Step is currently running (The body statements are running).
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>Done</Text><Enum>40</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Step has finished (The body statements are not running).
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>Error</Text><Enum>50</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Step is in error state. The sequencer does not execute any step logic.
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></EnumInfo><Properties><Property><Name>qualified_only</Name></Property><Property><Name>strict</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoCore">StepDetails</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Describes the status of a step of the sequencer.
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><BitSize>2144</BitSize><SubItem><Name>ID</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>0</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Order</Name><Type>UINT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>16</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Enabled</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>32</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Description</Name><Type>STRING(254)</Type><BitSize>2040</BitSize><BitOffs>40</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Status</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">eStepStatus</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>2080</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Duration</Name><Type>TIME</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>2112</BitOffs></SubItem></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoCore">eSequencerMode</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Modes of the sequencer.
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><BitSize>16</BitSize><BaseType>INT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text>Invalid</Text><Enum>-10</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Invalid, no logic is executed.
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>CyclicMode</Text><Enum>0</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Sequencer runs the steps of the sequence. 
			(When cyclic mode is selected, next step is automatically started after the previous one has been completed.)
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>StepMode</Text><Enum>10</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
		    Sequencer is in mode of step-by-step operation. The current step completes the execution regularly.
			In this mode the Step Forward/Backward and manual step execution is available.			
			<para>
				See <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoSequencerModeController.StepForward()"/> for detailed description.
				See <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoSequencerModeController.StepIn()"/> for detailed description.
				See <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoSequencerModeController.StepBackward()"/> for detailed description.
			</para>
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></EnumInfo><Properties><Property><Name>qualified_only</Name></Property><Property><Name>strict</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoSequencerModeController</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType GUID="{18071995-0000-0000-0000-000000000018}">PVOID</ExtendsType><Method><Name>__getMode</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>			
			Gets or sets sequencer mode.
			<remarks>			
				<para>
					See <see cref="TcoCore.eSequencerMode"/> for detailed description.
				</para>
			</remarks>		
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="TcoCore">eSequencerMode</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>16</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__setMode</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>			
			Gets or sets sequencer mode.
			<remarks>			
				<para>
					See <see cref="TcoCore.eSequencerMode"/> for detailed description.
				</para>
			</remarks>		
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>Mode</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>			
			Gets or sets sequencer mode.
			<remarks>			
				<para>
					See <see cref="TcoCore.eSequencerMode"/> for detailed description.
				</para>
			</remarks>		
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><Type Namespace="TcoCore">eSequencerMode</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>StepBackward</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			This method triggers StepBackward task, that decrements current step (variable: <c> TcoSequencer._theOrderOfTheCurrentlyExecutedStep</c> ), in case the sequencer is in step mode, and the current step is greather than zero.
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></Method><Method><Name>StepForward</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			This method triggers StepForward task, that increment current step (variable: <c>TcoSequencer._theOrderOfTheCurrentlyExecutedStep</c> ), 
			in case the sequencer is in step mode, and the current step is lower than number of steps in th sequence (variable: <c>TcoSequencer._numberOfStepsInSequence</c> ).
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></Method><Method><Name>StepIn</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Triggers StepIn task, that changes the current step status from ReadyToRun to Running. 
			This causes starting the execution of the body of the current step.
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></Method></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoSequencer</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoState</ExtendsType><Method><Name>__getCurrentStep</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Gets the information about the current step.						
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="TcoCore" ReferenceTo="true">StepDetails</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__getModeController</Name><ReturnType Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoSequencerModeController</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>Run</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			<para>
				Ensures calling the Open(), Main() and Close() methods in the desired order.
				This method is final, so it cannot be overloaded. The InstanceName.Run() needs to be called cyclically inside the appropriate context.
			</para>
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
